The paper deals with the design of dynamic data structures for interval coloring, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves graph theory concepts such as interval graphs and cliques, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses competitive ratio, which is a concept in game theory and optimization, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with online algorithms, which can be considered a subfield of machine learning, making cs.DL (Machine Learning) a less likely but still possible category.
